choices.text: a taboo topic, in part due to its potential impact on a family’s public reputation. Children are often expected to honor and support their parents until the moment they die, so the mother going against tradition by rejecting the spouse she raised from childhood increases families’ shame. As Oscar Wilde once said, “Whether it’s a man or a woman, the worst social disease that exists is divorce.”Predicaments like these often lead to further exploitation, but Ndiguel seizes opportunities where she sees them. Ju walks by Aissatou’s house every day on her way to school, leaving Aissatou with few options for escape. “He forces me to have sex with him,” she told Ndiguel, “and when he gives me money I give it to my mother to buy us food.”Ndiguel reached out to Aissatou’s mother, telling her that her daughter must first go to the hospital and receive a rape kit before she is interviewed by the authorities. When Aissatou’s mother went to collect her, she did not want to come but later agreed. After completing a medical exam, the pair reported the rape to the police and Ju was banned from the community for 10 years.Even with the help of Ndiguel, Ju and his family are unwilling to admit what happened and continue to use their wealth and influence to force Ju back into the community.
